This paper discusses the design and performance analysis of key-value stores, which are commonly used in database systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Database) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on the data structure and organization of key-value stores, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of fast storage devices such as SSDs and NVM is also discussed, which relates to cs.AR (Architecture). The paper also mentions the impact of device characteristics on KV-store design, which is relevant to cs.OS (Operating Systems). Finally, the paper proposes a new analysis technique for KV-store performance, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
